# Optional: a default Gemini API key baked into the build.
# When set, Luna defaults to the Gemini engine so a static deploy (GitHub Pages)
# works without each visitor adding their own key.
#
# ⚠️ SECURITY: a key in a client-side build is PUBLIC — anyone can read it from
# the deployed JavaScript. Use a key restricted to the Generative Language API
# with a low quota, or run a backend proxy for anything sensitive.
#
# Local dev: copy this file to ".env" (which is gitignored) and fill in the key.
# Production (GitHub Pages): add a repo secret named GEMINI_API_KEY instead — the
# deploy workflow passes it in as VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY at build time.

VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=
VITE_GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash
